# mode_wall sweep — 2026-05-31

Companion to `benchmarks/mode_wall_2026-05-31.csv` and
`benchmarks/mode_wall_2026-05-31.md`.

## Purpose

Task #157 Phase A: measure the Full-vs-Strip(-vs-StripPair) WALL-TIME +
peak-VRAM wall across all six umbrella metrics, both contexts (one-off and
warm/batch) and four sizes, to ground each metric's `resolve_auto` mode
selection in real numbers. Today every per-crate `resolve_auto`
(`crates/<metric>-gpu/src/memory_mode.rs`) is a memory-only heuristic
("Full when it fits the cap, else Strip" — except butter, which is
strip-preferred) resting on the UNMEASURED assumption that "Full is
fastest when it fits"; none consider StripPair. This sweep fills the
Full-vs-StripPair wall benchmark that `crates/cvvdp-gpu/docs/MODE_SELECTION.md`
mandated and left unfilled. MEASURE-only — no resolver change (Phase B).

## Provenance

- git commit (harness): `80deaa68eae4ebc05bbcd2050d902b7e6ca1a8cb`
  ("bench(zenmetrics): add mode_wall harness — Full/Strip/StripPair
  wall+VRAM sweep (task #157 Phase A)") on `master`.
- branched from `master@origin` 7fb4d8d6 ("feat(zenmetrics-api): add
  score_pair one-shot convenience").
- host: water-cooled AMD Ryzen 9 7950X + NVIDIA GeForce RTX 5070 (12 GB).
- CUDA SDK 13.2.1, driver 596.21, cubecl-cuda runtime (dlopen).
- GPU was SHARED with another process during the run (~1.5 GB resident,
  ~10.3 GB free at every cell start — recorded per-cell in
  `free_vram_start_mib`). No cell dropped below the 4 GB free-VRAM
  contention threshold, so VRAM peaks are clean reads; the
  `low_free_vram_at_start` note never fired. Timing is process-isolated
  and synced regardless of the sharer.

## Harness

`crates/zenmetrics-api/examples/mode_wall.rs` (subprocess-per-cell; the
parent enumerates the grid, spawns one child per cell, samples
`nvidia-smi memory.used` delta during the child's post-RESULT hold
window; the child computes synced wall percentiles and prints them).

Build (release, cuda, cubecl-types — NO target-cpu=native):

    PATH=/usr/local/cuda/bin:$PATH LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/cuda/lib64:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH \
    cargo build --release -p zenmetrics-api \
      --no-default-features --features cuda,all-metrics,cubecl-types,pixels \
      --example mode_wall

Run:

    MW_REPS=20 MW_SIZES=256,512,1024,4096 \
      target/release/examples/mode_wall > benchmarks/mode_wall_2026-05-31.csv

## Grid

- metrics × modes:
  - cvvdp: {Full, Strip (Mode E), StripPair (Mode B)}
  - ssim2, butter, dssim, iwssim: {Full, Strip}
  - zensim: {Full} (no strip path of its own)
  - CappedPyramid excluded (not JOD-identical, opt-in only).
- sizes: 256², 512², 1024², 4096² (tiny / small / medium / large).
- contexts:
  - one-off: construct a fresh metric + `compute_srgb_u8` one pair per
    rep (construction INSIDE the timed region; mirrors `score_pair` /
    `Metric::compute_srgb_u8`). One warmup construct+score before reps.
  - warm: `set_reference_srgb_u8` once, then time
    `compute_with_cached_reference_srgb_u8` per distinct dist (mirrors
    the orchestrator's cached-ref / batch path). One warmup score.
- n = 20 timed reps/cell; wall p25/p50/p75 reported.
- strip body height = 256 rows (power-of-two; matches
  `gpu_memory_audit_2026-05-27` so VRAM is comparable).
- backend: Cuda.

## How modes are forced

- Full / Strip: umbrella `Metric::new_with_memory_mode(kind, Cuda, w, h,
  params, mode)`.
- cvvdp StripPair: the umbrella `MemoryMode` enum has NO StripPair
  variant (it is a cvvdp-specific Mode B), so StripPair is forced via the
  typed `cvvdp_gpu::CvvdpOpaque::new_with_memory_mode(.., StripPair {
  h_body })`. This is the only reachable path; recorded in the harness
  module docs.

## Columns

`metric, mode, context, size, w, h, wall_ms_p25, wall_ms_p50,
wall_ms_p75, score, n, peak_vram_mib, free_vram_start_mib, note`

- `score`: the metric value for the (ref,dist) synthetic pair, carried so
  the parity check (mode score vs Full score) runs from the CSV.
- `peak_vram_mib`: peak `nvidia-smi memory.used` delta over the
  pre-launch baseline, sampled across the child's compute + 400 ms hold.
- `note`: `ok`, a SKIP/FAIL reason, or a flag
  (`cvvdp_oneoff_routes_full`, `strippair_warm_falls_back_mode_e`,
  `low_free_vram_at_start`).

## Known SKIP / FAIL cells (by design, not measurement gaps)

- `cvvdp/strip/oneoff/*` → SKIP. cvvdp Strip (Mode E) is a cached-ref-only
  path; a one-off `compute_srgb_u8` on a Strip-constructed cvvdp hits the
  Mode-E band loop with no `ref_full_state` cached and panics
  (`pipeline.rs:4963`). There is no valid cvvdp one-off Strip path.
- `cvvdp/strippair/warm/*` → FAIL ("image too small for the configured
  pyramid"). StripPair (Mode B) is a one-shot-pair mode with no cached
  ref of its own; warming it is a nonsensical combination and errors at
  all sizes. Flagged, not a correctness bug in a valid path.

The reference/distorted inputs are independent LCG-filled sRGB noise
(deterministic, seed-controlled). They are MAXIMALLY dissimilar, so
absolute metric values are at the far end of each scale (e.g. ssim2 goes
strongly negative, butter is large) — this is expected and irrelevant to
the wall/VRAM/parity questions (parity only requires the non-Full mode's
score to MATCH the Full mode's score on the same pair).
